  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "However, the landscape of NLP is ever-evolving, and recent developments have witnessed a surge in the exploration of larger and more intricate decoder-only models.Decoder-only models, such as GPT-3 [4], LaMDA [5], PaLM [6], GPT-4 [7] and LLaMA2 [8], have gained prominence due to their ability to generate human-quality text.",
    "Due to the large size of this new generation of models, these are called Large Language Models (LLM).",
    "These LLMs aim to learn probabilistic distributions over language, allowing them to generate new text similar to the training data.",
    "Interestingly, these models can also be effectively employed for intent classification and sentiment analysis.",
    "The decoder architecture, with its emphasis on language modeling, provides a unique perspective on extracting intent and sentiment from text.This paper aims to contribute to the ongoing discourse surrounding the selection of model architectures."
  ],
